name: Longstone Lighthouse (Outer Farne lighthouse) [Panoramic]
description:
Stunning photo taken of the beautiful Longstone Lighthouse. Located near the Farne Islands. Contrast of a rare calm sea against a brewing storm creates a unique view of northern waters. 

This lighthouse is famous for the story of Grace Darling. 

In the early hours of 7 September 1838, Grace, looking from an upstairs window of the Longstone Lighthouse on the Farne Islands, spotted the wreck and survivors of the Forfarshire on Big Harcar. The Forfarshire had foundered on the rocks and broken in half: one of the halves had sunk during the night. Grace and her father took a rowing boat out in the extreme weather to save the sailors as the weather was too dangerous for the lifeboat to arrive in time. Because of Grace and her father's brave efforts, 4 men and a lone woman survive the shipwreck which would have otherwise killed them.
